  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "The 13.1 and 26.2 stickers represent the distances of half marathons and marathons, respectively. Specifically:\n\n- **13.1**: This sticker indicates that a person has completed a half marathon, which is a distance of 13.1 miles (approximately 21.1 kilometers).\n- **26.2**: This sticker signifies that a person has completed a full marathon, which is a distance of 26.2 miles (approximately 42.2 kilometers).\n\nBoth stickers are often displayed on vehicles, water bottles, or personal belongings by runners as a way to show their accomplishment and dedication to long-distance running. They serve as a form of recognition for completing these challenging races.",
